---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Bingos — 50-Point Bonus Plays & Training"
  description="Master Scrabble bingos with guides on probability, stems, training methods, prefixes, suffixes, and the best 7-letter racks. Free guides, no signup."
  keywords="scrabble bingo, 50 point bonus, seven letter words scrabble, bingo stems, scrabble bingo probability, how to get bingos, bingo training scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is a bingo in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A bingo is when a player uses all 7 tiles from their rack in a single turn, earning a 50-point bonus on top of the word's regular score. Bingos are the fastest way to build a commanding lead and typically score 60-100+ total points per play." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How often should you get bingos in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Expert players average 2-3 bingos per game. Intermediate players typically get 0-1. The key factors are vocabulary size, rack management (keeping bingo-friendly tiles), and recognizing anagram patterns quickly under time pressure." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best tiles to keep for a bingo?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The most productive bingo tiles are S, E, R, A, N, T, I, and blank tiles. The SATIRE stem (any combination of these 6 letters plus one more) produces over 200 valid 7-letter words. Keeping 5-6 of these letters gives you the highest probability of drawing into a bingo." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 flex items-center gap-1">
      <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
      <span class="mx-1">›</span>
      <span class="text-gray-300">Bingos</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Bingos</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 mb-4">
      The 50-point bonus that separates good players from great ones. These 15 guides cover bingo probability, 
      productive stems, training methods, common prefixes and suffixes, rack building, and the psychology of 
      spotting 7-letter words under pressure. Learn to bingo consistently and your average score will jump 100+ points per game.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-gray-400 mb-8">
      A bingo — using all 7 tiles in a single turn — earns a 50-point bonus on top of the word's face value, routinely scoring 70-100+ points in one play. Tournament players average 2-3 bingos per game, and that's no accident. It comes from systematically learning productive stems (6-letter combinations that pair with many 7th letters), practising anagram recognition daily, and keeping bingo-friendly tiles on your rack even when shorter words score more immediately. The difference between a player who bingos once every 5 games and one who bingos twice per game is worth 150+ points across a match. These guides cover everything from the mathematical probability of drawing a bingo-capable rack to specific training exercises you can do in 10 minutes a day. Start with "What Is a Bingo" if you're new, or jump to stem strategy if you're ready to build your bingo repertoire systematically.
    </p>

    <div class="grid gap-4">
      <a href="/blog/what-is-a-bingo/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">What Is a Bingo?</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">The 50-point bonus explained — rules, scoring, and why bingos matter for competitive play.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/bingo-probability/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Bingo Probability</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">The mathematics behind bingos — how rack composition affects your chances of playing all 7 tiles.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/best-bingo-racks/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Bingo Racks</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">The highest-probability 7-tile combinations — racks that almost guarantee a bingo exists.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/bingo-stem-strategy/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Bingo Stem Strategy</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Build around productive stems like SATIRE and RETAIN — 6-letter bases that combine with many 7th tiles.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/bingo-training-methods/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Bingo Training Methods</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Drills, flashcards, anagram exercises, and study routines used by tournament players.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/common-bingo-prefixes/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Common Bingo Prefixes</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">RE-, UN-, OUT-, OVER-, MIS- — prefixes that extend words to 7+ letters for bonus plays.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/common-bingo-endings/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Common Bingo Endings</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">-ING, -TION, -ERS, -NESS, -ABLE — suffixes that turn shorter words into bingo-length plays.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/ing-words-scrabble-bingo/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">-ING Words for Scrabble Bingos</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">The most common bingo ending — keep ING on your rack and you're always one draw from a bonus.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/how-to-spot-bingos-faster/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">How to Spot Bingos Faster</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Pattern recognition techniques — rearranging tiles mentally, chunking, and using board hooks.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/highest-scoring-bingos/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Highest Scoring Bingos</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">The most valuable bingo plays possible — words that score 100+ points with the right board position.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/seven-letter-bingo-list/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Seven-Letter Bingo List</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">A curated list of the most playable 7-letter words organised by stem and probability.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/eight-letter-bingos/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Eight-Letter Bingos</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Playing through existing letters — how 8-letter bingos work and the most common opportunities.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/six-letter-words-that-lead-to-bingos/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Six-Letter Words That Lead to Bingos</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Words you can extend to 7+ letters by adding a single tile — set up your bingo one turn in advance.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/famous-tournament-bingos/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Famous Tournament Bingos</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">Iconic bingo plays from championship games — the words that decided titles and set records.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/highest-scoring-seven-letter-words/" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Highest Scoring Seven-Letter Words</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">The 7-letter words with the highest base tile values — maximise your bingo bonus points.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 border-t border-gray-800 pt-8">
      <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">More Categories</h3>
      <div class="grid gap-3">
        <a href="/blog/strategy/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
          <span class="text-blue-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Strategy — Advanced tactics and rack management</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/high-scoring/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
          <span class="text-blue-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">High-Scoring Words — The most valuable plays in Scrabble</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/tournament/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
          <span class="text-blue-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Tournament & Competitive — Compete at the highest level</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/two-letter-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
          <span class="text-blue-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Two-Letter Words — Master the 127 essential short words</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-indigo-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
        <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">
          🔤 Find bingo words instantly with our free Scrabble solver — enter 7+ tiles
        </p>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">
